@node "iNSTALLATiON" "iNSTALLATiON"
@toc "main"
  -» iNSTALLATiON «-
 +------------------+
 Copy <lZXSTRIP.list> and <lZXSTRIP.wild> to <s:>
 Copy <lZXstrip> to <c:>
 (BBS owners: copy LZXstrip_TEMPEST to <c:> as well)
@endnode

@node "uSAGE" "uSAGE"
@toc "main"
  -» uSAGE «-
 +-----------+
 lZXStrip <LZX-ARCHIVE>

 NOTE:  If you want to use lZXStrip with Dopus just make a new
        entry as an AmigaDOS command and type
        <c:LZXstrip {s}{o}>
        (you may have selected another path!)

 NOTE:  NEW IN VERSION v1.o5 bETA : <c:LZXstrip {f}>
        WORKS NOW !!! ALSO STRIPPING FROM <RAM DISK:>

@endnode

@node "bBS uSAGE" "bBS uSAGE"
@toc "main"
  -» bBS uSAGE «-
 +---------------+
 There is a special version for Tempest called <LZXstrip_TEMPEST>.
 This one may be used with any other BBS-Program. If you write
 a script for another BBS-Program please send it to me.
 The BBS-Version has the same template as the normal version.

 Usage with Tempest : 1. just copy the file <Scripts/Strip_lzx> to
                         <TEMPEST:Scripts/>
                         (Be careful the old file <Strip_lzx> gets
                         lost)
                      2. copy LZXstrip_TEMPEST to <c:>
                         Copy <lZXSTRIP.list> and <lZXSTRIP.wild> 
                         to <s:>
                         wELL dONE !!!

 If you want to use this program with a BBS-Program, contact me
 @{"(the Author)" link "tHE aUTHOR" 0} to get a special registered Version (for FREE !)
 I just want to know how many people use my program ;-) .
@endnode

@node "tHE bRAiNFiLES" "tHE bRAiNFiLES"
@toc "main"
  -» tHE bRAiNFiLES «-
 +--------------------+
 There are 2 brainfiles. One for wildcard and one normal stripping.
 You can edit the brainfiles to add new bbs-adds you want to strip,
 but ensure that there is no BLANK line in the brainfiles !!
 Put only one filename in each line and remember, it takes more
 time to check the archives if you add lots of new names to
 the brainfiles.
 THIS OPTION IS NO MORE CASE SENSITIVE !!!


 a) The normal Brainfile (<lZXSTRIP.list>):

  Examples: 1. you want to strip <xTassy.bbs> from an archive.
               right: add <xTassy.bbs> to lZXSTRIP.list
               right: add <XtAsSy.bBs> to lZXSTRIP.list
               wrong: add <xTassy.bbs#?> to lZXSTRIP.list

            2. there is an add like <spirit!of!soul/JU6.dunno.V13> in
               the archive.
               So you just add <spirit!of!soul/JU6.dunno.V13> .

            3. you want to strip <      .nfo> from an archive.
               right: add <      .nfo> to lZXSTRIP.list
               wrong: add <    .nfo> to lZXSTRIP.list
               wrong: add <.nfo> to to lZXSTRIP.list
               wrong: add <"      .nfo"> to lZXSTRIP.list

  The easiest way to get the correct names, is to list the lzx.archive
  and then snap the full name and path of the file you want to strip.


 b) The wildcard stripfile (<lZXSTRIP.wild>):

  Examples: 1. you want to strip all files that end with <.displayme>
               right: add <.displayme> to lZXSTRIP.wild
               wrong: add <#?.displayme#?> to lZXSTRIP.wild
                      (the wildcards were added automatically,
                       in fact the stripper wont work correct if
                       you add them in the lZXSTRIP.wild-barinfile)
            2. you want to kill all files in the directory
               <spirit!of!soul>.
               right: add <spirit!of!soul> to lZXSTRIP.wild
               wrong: add <spirit!of!soul/#?> to lZXSTRIP.list

 CAUTION: NEVER ADD A FILENAME LIKE <[.tHE.bOARD.]> TO lZXSTRIP.wild
          THIS WOULD DELETE THE ENTIRE ARCHIVE !
          WHY ??? ASK THE PROGRAMMERS OF LZX !!! NOT MY FAULT ...
          SOLUTION:   1. add <[.tHE.bOARD.]> to lzxstrip.list
                         (with full path)
                      2. just add <.tHE.bOARD.]> , <[.tHE.bOARD.>
                         or <.tHE.bOARD.> to lzxstrip.wild

 NOTE: Names containing <|> won`t be stripped. Why ???
       AGAIN: ASK THE PROGRAMMERS OF LZX !!! NOT MY FAULT ...
       Example:  <.| 5 NODES OF PURE HARDCORE |> won`t be stripped
       SOLUTION: add <5 NODES OF PURE HARDCORE> to lzxstrip.wild

 NOTE: You may use the brainfiles from IStrip, but you have to copy
       them and rename them into <lZXSTRIP.list> and <lZXSTRIP.wild>

@endnode

@node "hiSTORY" "hiSTORY"
@toc "main"
  -» hiSTORY «-
 +-------------+
 lZXStrip v1.o bETA   (o2.o1.96)  - First public release (STILL BETA !)

 lZXStrip v1.ot bETA  (o3.o1.96)  - Fixed Version for TEMPEST
                                    (other BBS-Programs)

 lZXStrip v1.o1 bETA  (xx.xx.xx)  - never released :)

 lZXStrip v1.o2 bETA  (xx.o1.96)  - Added wildcards
                                  - Bugfixes (did not work w/ evulation
                                              version :-( !!!)
                                  - Speed improvements
                                  - Fixed some "BUGS" in the docfile
                                    (biG thX tO ACE !!! ;-))

 lZXStrip v1.o2t bETA (xx.o1.96)  - BBS-Version (espacially for
                                                 /T\empest !!!)
                                  - same as v1.o2 bETA
 lZXStrip v1.o3 bETA  (2o.o1.96)  - SPEEDUP !!!
                                  - Removed case sensity
                                  - Compiled the ARexx scripts

 lZXStrip v1.o3t bETA (2o.o1.96)  - Same as v1.o3 bETA
                                  - Little bugfix

 lZXStrip v1.o4 bETA  (25.o1.96)  - Speedup especially with larger
                                    archives
                                  - New outfit

 lZXStrip v1.o4t bETA (25.o1.96)  - Same as v1.o4 bETA

 lZXStrip v1.o5  bETA (18.o2.96)  - Bugfixes (filenames containing
                                    spaces will now be recognized)
                                  - PUBLIC VERSION IS NOW
                                    UNREGISTERED ! -> GET REGISTERED
                                  - Fixed a bug with Dopus
                                  - Supports now stripping adds including
                                    spaces

 lZXStrip v1.o5t bETA (18.o2.96)  - Version for BBS-usage

@endnode

